    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Rear Air Suspension Assembly</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Rear Air Suspension Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain air from the air system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the air line to the rear cab air suspension assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the rear bench seat. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603804.xml" xrefid="x1603804">
                        <emph type="bold">REAR BENCH SEAT</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603804"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove seat belt mounting bolts (not shown) securing seat belts to rear cab floor. Lift
                    up floor mat to access carriage bolts in cab underbody sill.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The carriage bolts are secured to the cab underbody sill with cab mount retaining clips. The
                        carriage bolts will remain with cab underbody sill when cab is lifted off the rear cab air
                        suspension assembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f16038115" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G16038115.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 140. Air Suspension Mounting Carriage Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CARRIAGE BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB UNDERBODY SILL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RETAINING CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REAR CAB AIR SUSPENSION ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift up carriage bolts through cab underbody sill and unscrew from retaining clips.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the carriage bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f16038114" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G16038114.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 141. Rear Air Suspension Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REAR CAB AIR SUSPENSION ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. AIR LINE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRAME RAIL CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four nuts and four bolts securing rear cab air suspension assembly to frame rail
                    crossmember.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a suitable lifting device between frame and back of cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise cab and remove rear cab air suspension assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear cab air suspension assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f16038114">Figure 141, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four nuts and four bolts securing rear cab air suspension assembly to frame rail
                    crossmember (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f16038114">Figure 141</hotlnk>). Tighten nuts to 88 to 106 Lbf-ft (119 to 144 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the air line to the rear cab air suspension assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f16038114">Figure 141, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower rear of cab onto rear air suspension and remove lifting device.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the carriage bolts through the cab floor and cab underbody sill (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f16038115">Figure 140, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Screw retaining clips onto both carriage bolts until they are against the bottom of the
                    cab underbody sill (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f16038115">Figure 140</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reposition the floor mat and install seat belt mounting bolts (not shown) securing seat
                    belts to rear cab floor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rear bench seat. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603804.xml" xrefid="x1603804">
                        <emph type="bold">REAR BENCH SEAT</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603804"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
